next runner-up, until covered, then cut to fit, never repeating a clip (Rule v27.0), and it understands niche TERMINOLOGY (tunneling, borehole, sinkhole, frosting…) via an offline per-niche glossary so jargon matches the footage that shows it and the terms appear in descriptions (Rule v28.0). The corpus is a COLLABORATIVE git repo — many Cowork/Code chats clone/pull/push, conflict-free (one file per video), no lost work (Rule v28.2); a SHA-256 manifest + optional `drive_sync verify` keep an optional Drive mirror checksum-verified (Rule v28.1). All v22 behaviour is inherited:
